<subSubSection pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,1891,2037]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1891,1917]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species is similar in general appearance to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[861,1013,1892,1917]" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" genus="Verodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis box="[861,1013,1892,1917]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">V. inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from that species by having 6 distinct nodules in the apical half of the elytra not connected to ridges versus 3 or 
<quantity box="[1361,1407,1931,1957]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" genus="Verodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">V. inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
